				</ukm:Metadata><Primary><Body DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/body" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/body" NumberOfProvisions="374" RestrictExtent="E+W+S+N.I." RestrictStartDate="2026-05-18"><Part DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/part/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/part/1" NumberOfProvisions="108" id="part-1" RestrictExtent="E+W+S+N.I." RestrictStartDate="2026-03-18"><Number>Part 1</Number><Title>Income tax, capital gains tax and corporate taxes</Title><Pblock DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/part/1/crossheading/income-tax-charge-rates-and-allowances" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/part/1/crossheading/income-tax-charge-rates-and-allowances" NumberOfProvisions="14" RestrictStartDate="2026-03-18" id="part-1-crossheading-income-tax-charge-rates-and-allowances" RestrictExtent="E+W+S+N.I."><Title>Income tax charge, rates and allowances</Title><P1group RestrictStartDate="2026-03-18" RestrictExtent="E+W+S+N.I."><Title>Basic rate limit and personal allowance for tax years 2028-29 to 2030-31</Title><P1 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/section/10" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/section/10" id="section-10"><Pnumber>10</Pnumber><P1para><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/1" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/1" id="section-10-1"><Pnumber>1</Pnumber><P2para><Text>Section 5 of FA 2021 (basic rate limit and personal allowance for tax years up to 2027-28) is amended as follows.</Text></P2para></P2><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/2" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/2" id="section-10-2"><Pnumber>2</Pnumber><P2para><Text>In subsection (1) (which specifies the basic rate limit in section 10(5) of ITA 2007 as £37,700 for tax years up to 2027-28), for “and 2027-28” substitute <InlineAmendment>“, 2027-28, 2028-29, 2029-30 and 2030-31”</InlineAmendment>.</Text></P2para></P2><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/3" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/3" id="section-10-3"><Pnumber>3</Pnumber><P2para><Text>In subsection (2) (which specifies the personal allowance in section 35(1) of ITA 2007 as £12,570 for tax years up to 2027-28), for “and 2027-28” substitute <InlineAmendment>“, 2027-28, 2028-29, 2029-30 and 2030-31”</InlineAmendment>.</Text></P2para></P2><P2 DocumentURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/4" IdURI="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/id/ukpga/2026/11/section/10/4" id="section-10-4"><Pnumber>4</Pnumber><P2para><Text>In subsection (3) (which makes consequential provision preventing the uprating of those amounts for the affected tax years), in the words after paragraph (b), for “and 2027-28” substitute <InlineAmendment>“, 2027-28, 2028-29, 2029-30 and 2030-31”</InlineAmendment>.</Text></P2para></P2></P1para></P1></P1group></Pblock></Part></Body></Primary></Legislation>